# Privacy policy

Webconverger is designed to ensure users privacy and [[security]] whilst
surfing the Web.

Webconverger limited (the company) does not currently collect any information
about how you use Webconverger.  Earlier versions (before 2.31) were collecting
version, boot parameters (e.g. homepage=) and MAC information.

All *.webconverger.[com|org] sites have standard [Apache](http://apache.org/)
logs, which will log you if you visit that site. Logs are typically rotated
(deleted) within a year.

Webconverger.org is using [Google analytics](https://www.google.com/analytics/)

If you are concerned about your privacy, use Webconverger. :-)
